 <methods> <methodStep> <description> <section> <title>Artificial clipping</title>
 <para>We selected 6 different sites with different histories of attack from large ungulate browsers. We then selected 5 trees per site and on each tree 12 randomly located terminal shoots were clipped in the late growing season. A tagged was located on the remaining shoot and a new clipping was performed 9 months later the first clipping.</para>
 </section>
